str2: To take in hand, attempt. From epi and cheir; to put the hand upon, i.e. Undertake.
From ana and the middle voice of tasso; to arrange.
A narrative. From diegeomai; a recital.
From the base of peran; properly, through, i.e. Around; figuratively with respect to; used in various applications, of place, cause or time.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A thing done, a deed, action; a matter, an affair. From prasso; a deed; by implication, an affair; by extension, an object.

str2: From pleres and phoreo; to carry out fully, i.e. Completely assure, entirely accomplish.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
